Date:  18/4/1902
Source:  Bruce Herald
Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  The nest of the tree cricket is very interesting; the eggs are laid in the pith of raspberry stalks and grape shoots, and as the mother must bore through the tough stem, lay the egg and then close the opening with fluids from her mouth, the amount of work performed by her is incredible.
